---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumbs from '../components/layout/Breadcrumbs.astro';
import { SITE_URL } from '../lib/utils';

const lastUpdated = '5 April 2025';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cookie Policy – EasyDeutschKitchen"
  description="Learn about how EasyDeutschKitchen.com uses cookies, including analytics and advertising cookies. Find out how to manage or disable cookies in your browser."
  canonicalURL={`${SITE_URL}/cookies/`}
>
  <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <Breadcrumbs crumbs={[{ label: 'Cookie Policy' }]} />

    <div class="mb-10">
      <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Cookie Policy</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-gray-500">Last updated: <time datetime="2025-04-05">{lastUpdated}</time></p>
      <div class="mt-4 p-4 bg-amber-50 border-l-4 border-amber-500 rounded-r-xl text-sm text-amber-900">
        This policy explains what cookies are, which ones we use, and how you can control them. We believe you have the right to know exactly what is happening on your device when you visit our site.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4 prose-h3:text-lg prose-h3:mt-6 prose-p:text-gray-700 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-li:text-gray-700 prose-a:text-amber-700 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline prose-strong:text-gray-900">

      <h2>1. What Are Cookies?</h2>
      <p>
        Cookies are small text files placed on your device (computer, tablet, or smartphone) when you visit a website. They allow the website — or third-party services — to recognise your device on future visits and remember certain information, such as your preferences or browsing behaviour.
      </p>
      <p>
        Cookies are widely used across the web to make websites work efficiently, to improve user experience, and to provide information to website owners and advertisers. They do not contain viruses or malicious code.
      </p>

      <h2>2. How We Use Cookies</h2>
      <p>EasyDeutschKitchen.com uses cookies for the following purposes:</p>
      <ul>
        <li>To understand how visitors use the site so we can improve it (analytics)</li>
        <li>To display relevant advertising and support the free operation of the blog (advertising)</li>
        <li>To remember basic preferences where applicable (functional)</li>
      </ul>

      <h2>3. Types of Cookies We Use</h2>

    </div>

    <!-- Cookie table -->
    <div class="my-8 space-y-4">

      <!-- Essential -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-4 bg-green-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-green-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Essential Cookies</h3>
          <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-semibold text-green-700 bg-green-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Always Active</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
          <p>These cookies are necessary for the website to function and cannot be disabled. They do not store any personally identifiable information.</p>
          <table class="w-full text-xs border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Cookie</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Expiry</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">__cf_bm</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Cloudflare</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Bot management & DDoS protection</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">30 minutes</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">cf_clearance</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Cloudflare</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Security challenge verification</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">30 minutes</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Analytics -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-4 bg-blue-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-blue-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Analytics Cookies</h3>
          <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-semibold text-blue-700 bg-blue-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Requires Consent</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
          <p>These cookies help us understand how visitors interact with the website by collecting and reporting information anonymously. This data helps us improve our content and user experience.</p>
          <table class="w-full text-xs border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Cookie</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Expiry</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">_ga</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Distinguishes unique users</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">_ga_XXXXXXXX</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Session state persistence</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">2 years</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">_gid</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google Analytics</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Stores and counts page views</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">24 hours</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Google Analytics data is processed in accordance with <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-amber-700 underline">Google's Privacy Policy</a>. We have enabled IP anonymisation for all analytics tracking.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Advertising -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-4 bg-orange-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-orange-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Advertising Cookies</h3>
          <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-semibold text-orange-700 bg-orange-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Requires Consent</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
          <p>These cookies are used to deliver advertisements that are relevant to you and your interests. They also help us measure the effectiveness of advertising campaigns. They may be placed by Google AdSense or other advertising networks we work with.</p>
          <table class="w-full text-xs border-collapse">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Cookie</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Provider</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Purpose</th>
                <th class="text-left px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-semibold">Expiry</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">IDE</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google / DoubleClick</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Personalised ad targeting & measurement</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">13 months</td>
              </tr>
              <tr class="bg-gray-50">
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">DSID</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google / DoubleClick</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Ad personalisation across devices</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">2 weeks</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200 font-mono">NID</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">Google ads personalisation</td>
                <td class="px-3 py-2 border border-gray-200">6 months</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
          <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">Google uses these cookies to show ads based on your previous visits to this and other websites. You can opt out of personalised advertising by visiting <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-amber-700 underline">Google Ads Settings</a>.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <!-- Social -->
      <div class="border border-gray-200 rounded-2xl overflow-hidden">
        <div class="flex items-center gap-3 px-5 py-4 bg-purple-50 border-b border-gray-200">
          <span class="w-3 h-3 rounded-full bg-purple-500 shrink-0"></span>
          <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900">Social Media Cookies</h3>
          <span class="ml-auto text-xs font-semibold text-purple-700 bg-purple-100 px-2 py-0.5 rounded-full">Third-Party</span>
        </div>
        <div class="px-5 py-4 text-sm text-gray-700 space-y-3">
          <p>Social share buttons (Pinterest, Facebook, Twitter/X) on recipe pages may load scripts from those platforms that set their own cookies. These are governed by the respective platform's privacy policies and are outside our direct control.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

    </div>

    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-none prose-headings:font-bold prose-headings:text-gray-900 prose-h2:text-2xl prose-h2:mt-10 prose-h2:mb-4 prose-p:text-gray-700 prose-p:leading-relaxed prose-li:text-gray-700 prose-a:text-amber-700 prose-a:no-underline hover:prose-a:underline prose-strong:text-gray-900">

      <h2>4. Your Consent and How to Manage Cookies</h2>
      <p>
        Under the GDPR and the EU ePrivacy Directive, we are required to obtain your consent before placing non-essential cookies on your device. When you first visit EasyDeutschKitchen, you will be presented with a cookie consent notice where you can accept or decline categories of cookies.
      </p>
      <p>You can manage cookies in several ways:</p>

      <h3>Browser Settings</h3>
      <p>Most browsers allow you to view, manage, block, or delete cookies. Here are links to instructions for common browsers:</p>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Google Chrome:</strong> Settings → Privacy and Security → Cookies and other site data</li>
        <li><strong>Mozilla Firefox:</strong> Settings → Privacy & Security → Cookies and Site Data</li>
        <li><strong>Safari:</strong> Preferences → Privacy → Manage Website Data</li>
        <li><strong>Microsoft Edge:</strong> Settings → Cookies and site permissions</li>
      </ul>
      <p>
        Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect the functionality of the website or result in less relevant advertising.
      </p>

      <h3>Google Ad Personalisation</h3>
      <p>
        You can opt out of Google's use of cookies for personalised advertising by visiting <a href="https://adssettings.google.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Ads Settings</a> or by using the <a href="https://optout.networkadvertising.org/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">NAI opt-out tool</a>.
      </p>

      <h3>Google Analytics Opt-Out</h3>
      <p>
        You can prevent Google Analytics from collecting your data by installing the <a href="https://tools.google.com/dlpage/gaoptout" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Google Analytics Opt-out Browser Add-on</a>.
      </p>

      <h2>5. Do Not Track</h2>
      <p>
        Some browsers include a "Do Not Track" (DNT) feature that sends a signal to websites you visit expressing your preference not to be tracked. Currently, there is no industry-wide standard for responding to DNT signals, and EasyDeutschKitchen does not alter its data collection practices in response to DNT signals. We will monitor developments in this area and update our practices accordingly.
      </p>

      <h2>6. Updates to This Policy</h2>
      <p>
        We may update this Cookie Policy periodically to reflect changes in technology, legislation, or our own practices. When we make changes, we will revise the "last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this page on each visit.
      </p>

      <h2>7. Questions</h2>
      <p>
        If you have questions about our use of cookies or this Cookie Policy, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a> or email <a href="mailto:privacy@easydeutschkitchen.com">privacy@easydeutschkitchen.com</a>.
      </p>

    </div>

    <div class="mt-12 p-5 bg-gray-50 rounded-2xl border border-gray-200 text-sm text-gray-600">
      <p class="font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-2">Legal Pages</p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
        <a href="/privacy/" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Privacy Policy</a>
        <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
        <a href="/terms/" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Terms of Service</a>
        <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
        <a href="/disclaimer/" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Disclaimer</a>
        <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
        <a href="/cookies/" class="text-amber-700 font-medium underline">Cookie Policy</a>
        <span class="text-gray-300">|</span>
        <a href="/contact/" class="text-amber-700 hover:underline">Contact</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
